# Walkthrough - Smart Tracking for Organic Articles

I have successfully implemented the "Smart Tracking" solution. This system allows you to maintain clean, SEO-friendly internal links while ensuring your IT system receives the critical `typedealer` parameter for lead attribution.

## Changes

### 1. Replica Article ([index.html](file:///Users/weerachitbuaim/Documents/TEST_WEB/index.html))
I created a replica of the "2+ vs 3+" article with standard, clean HTML links.
- **Before Click**: `href="form-mock.html"` (Clean, SEO-friendly)
- **Slug Configuration**: Added `<meta name="article-slug" content="difference-2plus-vs-3plus">`

### 2. Tracking Script ([tracking.js](file:///Users/weerachitbuaim/Documents/TEST_WEB/tracking.js))
This script automatically:
1. Detects links with the class `.internal-link`.
2. Intercepts the click event.
3. Appends `?typedealer=organic_{article-slug}`.
4. Navigates the user to the destination.

### 3. Mock Destination ([form-mock.html](file:///Users/weerachitbuaim/Documents/TEST_WEB/form-mock.html))
A simple page to verify that parameters are being passed correctly.

